# Project-local (user) Bazel configuration — git-ignored, personal to you.
# Loaded last via `try-import %workspace%/user.bazelrc` from the repo's .bazelrc,
# so anything here overrides committed defaults.
#
# Easiest: run `bazel run //tools/remote:setup` to pick a build cache interactively.
# Or copy this file to `user.bazelrc` and uncomment ONE cache option below.
# See docs/build-cache.md.

# Keep Bazel's user root + cache off the workspace (handy in containers):
# startup --output_user_root=/tmp/bazel-cache

# --- Build cache (pick at most one; default is none) -----------------------

# 1) local — disk cache on THIS machine only (use an absolute path):
# common --disk_cache=/tmp/bazel-disk-cache

# 2) shared — your team's self-hosted bazel-remote (read-only; CI writes).
#    If it is unreachable, builds fall back to local automatically:
# common --remote_cache=grpcs://cache.example.com
# common --remote_upload_local_results=false

# 3) buildbuddy — cache + remote execution. Run `bazel run //tools/remote:setup`
#    first to store the API key, then enable it (only when online):
# common --config=remote
